1. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper focuses on the Koopman operator, which is a tool commonly used in systems and control theory. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper introduces a deep learning framework for learning Koopman operators, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of deep learning in this paper also falls under the category of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper specifically uses deep neural networks to learn Koopman operators, which falls under the category of neural computing. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): While not the main focus of the paper, the use of dictionaries and basis sets in the extended dynamic mode decomposition could potentially fall under the category of data structures and algorithms.
